Global Concrete for Tunnelling Market Insights
Concrete for Tunnelling Market size was valued at USD 15.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 22.4 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.3% from 2024 to 2030.

Concrete for Tunnelling Market Overview
The concrete for tunnelling market has been experiencing robust growth, driven by the increasing demand for infrastructure development, particularly in transportation networks such as railways, metros, and highways. As of 2024, the market is valued at USD 8.3 billion and is projected to reach USD 12.5 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.1% during the forecast period. The tunnelling sector requires high-performance concrete materials that offer durability, strength, and flexibility under extreme conditions. The concrete used in tunnelling must be resilient against water penetration and ground pressure while adhering to strict safety standards.

